| !SQLite !Boot file
| RISC OS application boot script
| Sets up environment and memory allocation
|
| This file is run when the application is first seen by the file manager

| Set up application path
Set SQLite$Dir <Obey$Dir>

| Configure memory
| WimpSlot sets the minimum and maximum memory for the application
| Format: WimpSlot -min <minimum>K -max <maximum>K
|
| SQLite requirements:
|   Minimum: 2MB for safe operation
|   Maximum: 4MB to stay within system limits
|   Target: 2-3MB for typical databases

WimpSlot -min 2048K -max 3072K

| End of !Boot
